                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">In fact we've been told it can't be done. Well now it can.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br />And since it can be done now and it couldn't be done when Luclin was released when the SCF AA was created, why is it so hard to expect that an advantage/power/ability that was given to casters of Direct Damage spells be given to those who cast DoT's? If Monks had a coding issue with haste because they were using bare hands as weapons, should Monks who choose to use bare hands now be penalized because of a previous coding limitation versus other melees? <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">"We SHOULD get the SAME crit chance on dots EVERY nuking class get on nukes..." Why? My DoT's are not the same as a nuke. DoT's are only a part of my abilities.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br />Correct, and guess what as a Necromancer you have the ability to purchase AA abilites that allow you to crit on both. Why should your DoT crit AA's cost so much more for so much less utility? Why not play a warrior that gets only half his damage if he uses a 1hb vs 1hs? Why not make it so that every piercer is only doing half the damage it would normally do if its being wielded by a rogue?<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Every time I hear "We have to have 13% DoTs because nukers have 13% nukes" all I hear is a little rich kid complaining that the poor kid down the street has a $110 bicycle, but the rich kid only got a $100 bicycle.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"> Lets not be stupid here, one kid got a $110 bicycle that cost him $110, the other kid got $55 dollar bicycle that cost him $110. You think thats fair? <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Its not fair, poor kid is better than me, we SHOULD be equal. Maybe even better because I've had to do without a bicycle for so long.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"> <br />Quote me in this thread where someone who isn't a complete moron says we should get a bigger % chance to crit for the same amount of AA. Perhaps your reading what you want to see in this thread.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> Guess if I wasn't that little rich kid playing the best class in EQ I might feel differently.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br />This reminds me of all the 13 year olds who used to start threads on this board daily about how 'l337 it is to be the evil bastards' and 'if you dont hate dr00ds you aint a real necro'. Perhaps if you knew how to play a necro, really knew how to play a necro and stopped eating that line of shit SoE has been feeding you, you might see some of the issues we been talking bout. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Would I love for SOE to ignore everything else I can do and make my crits equal to everyone else, YES! Do I think I have some inescapable right to it, NO!<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />So first everyone here is a whiny bitch child for wanting to be equal, now you want to be equal but your not a whiny bitch? Just because you dont think you have an 'inescapable right to it'? I tell you what, every time you earn an AA point from now on, you have to lose an entire bar of regular exp (meaning all of it) and then earn it back before you can earn a new AA point. Go ahead and tell me how much fun thats going to be. That would be the same as you rolling over and not fighting for equity with DD casters in the AA department. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">3) I also don't think we should get maximum DoT crits in a single expansion. I have no idea if suddenly every high-end Necro is now doing 13-15% more damage for all their DoT's will unbalance the game. <hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />Its not our fault the game devs took forever to figure out how to find and display dot damage. Its not our fault they never listened to anyone who had been screaming for these changes for years. Fuck yeah I want them to put them in all at once. I don't want to have to wait for another fucking expansion and 30 bucks for something they should have done years ago. When Luclin came out we should have gotten Critical Affliction. I been waiting that long already, fuck waiting for more. <br /><br />As for unbalancing the game: A lot of the end-PoP content is mob health percentage driven. Drop too many nukes that crit for too much now and you screw the raid. Same thing will happen to DoT casters. We will have to adjust. How is a nuke that hits normally for 2500 (or whatever) and crits for 5k+ in a single instant so less unbalancing to the game than a dot that would normally do 2500 over the course of 30 seconds suddenly upped to 5k? If the DD crit wasnt unbalancing neither is the DoT crit. <br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"> I believe the game is more healthy than that and would prefer to see DoT crits get introduced over a couple of expansions, as was done with DD crits. So 7% now, another 7% later is the prudent way to increase Necro power rather than just upping it all at once.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote"><br /><br />This is the biggest line of bull shit I think Ive ever seen. I swear, you must be Absor in disguise. Oh Sony, please charge us for another expansion with AA's that should have been in the game 4 expansions ago. We know you didnt know how to do it before and now that you do its perfectly ok to let DoT casters lag behind even longer cuz, you know, uhm.. classes are balanced and all that fluffy shit.</span id="msg"></font></td>
