                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Hey I'm posting on the Necro board, I expect to get hurt.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">Just so you're prepared...<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">1) I expect GoD AA's to cost more. SCF came out pre-PoP, it was much more work to get 12AA's. 12AA's today is a joke to all you Uber Necros that like to make fun of me. In order to make a Crit DoT equal to the work it would have taken to get this pre-PoP it just has to cost more. That I consider to be fair. Good for me, god no, but fair. Someone who got SCF3 when it first came out worked hard to get it. If CritDoT costs the same, you'll hardly work at all to get it.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">So because AAs are easier to get now, we should devalue them?  Sorry, no.  An AA is an AA is an AA.  I expect my AAs to have the same relative value as other people's AAs.  Asking me to spend 30AAs to get the same relative benefit that someone else CAN STILL GET for 12 AAs isn't fair.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Arguing that we should have got it in the first place is just sour grapes to me. We didn't, its new, and I don't agree it should be retroactively priced, its not like we've been promised it all this time. In fact we've been told it can't be done. Well now it can.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">Yeah, I guess it is sour grapes, but we've been watching nuke damage skyrocket for so long some of us are more than a little frustrated.  Don't call it retroactive pricing though, it's not.  All we want is our 7% crit chance to cost the same as everyone elses 7% crit chance.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">2) "We SHOULD get the SAME crit chance on dots EVERY nuking class get on nukes..." Why? My DoT's are not the same as a nuke. DoT's are only a part of my abilities. Maybe at the high-end all we ever cast are DoTs, but I don't. And there are quite a few Necros that are not "high end". You cannot take one skill of a class and say that skill SHOULD be the SAME as another class out of isolation of everything else the class can do. I think it takes a lot more than profanity to convince me. Nukers can have more DPS than me, either through crits or base damage, I DO NOT HAVE TO BE THE SAME.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">Then you really don't understand class balance very well.  In many ways, class balance is sameness (on some level at least).  We don't do damage in the same manner as nukers, but we preform the same function (i.e. damage).  We should have the same oppurtunity to improve our damage abilities through AAs as other classes...that's balance.<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">Every time I hear "We have to have 13% DoTs because nukers have 13% nukes" all I hear is a little rich kid complaining that the poor kid down the street has a $110 bicycle, but the rich kid only got a $100 bicycle. Its not fair, poor kid is better than me, we SHOULD be equal. Maybe even better because I've had to do without a bicycle for so long. Guess if I wasn't that little rich kid playing the best class in EQ I might feel differently.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">Bad analogy.  It would be closer to say we're being asked to pay $300 for the same $110 bicycle because we want a blue one (dots) instead of red (nukes).<br /><br /><blockquote id="quote"><font size="1" face="trebuchet ms,tahoma" id="quote">quote:<hr height="1" noshade id="quote">3) I also don't think we should get maximum DoT crits in a single expansion. I have no idea if suddenly every high-end Necro is now doing 13-15% more damage for all their DoT's will unbalance the game. Normal argument is that EQ is broken so you can't break it more, or who cares if it makes us overpowered, or Waldina's retarded again to think 13% more damage changes anything. I believe the game is more healthy than that and would prefer to see DoT crits get introduced over a couple of expansions, as was done with DD crits. So 7% now, another 7% later is the prudent way to increase Necro power rather than just upping it all at once.<hr height="1" noshade id="quote"></font id="quote"></blockquote id="quote">I don't think we should necessarily get all 13% in ONE AA LINE.  I'd be perfectly happy if they introduced several levels of AA lines mirroring the DD lines that slowly ramped up the crit%.  However, there is really no reason they couldn't add multiple crit DoT AA lines all right now...why wait for several expansions to catch up?<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
