                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I started reading this beast thread with the thought in my mind that I wanted more levels of crit affliction. I can see where you are all coming from including Waldina.<br /><br />I used to use my parser quite alot. Before all LDoN adventures I would tell the group i was parsing, and would make it seem like a bit of a competition on who could do the most damage, even the clerics would load up their nukes etc, more dmg means quicker adventure hehe. On some raid targets I would do the same thing.<br /><br />At my level (elemental but not time) Ive always achieved around the same as, or outdamaged any wizard/rogue of my level in gear, maybe cause I was trying really hard, maybe cause every wizard ive grouped with is crap.<br /><br />I guess my concern is, in this expansion they are giving us aas to increase our pets dmg, giving us aas to crit dots and an additional level of crit nukes. All of that will add up to something like a 5 to 7% increase in our dmg if I've read correctly (i'm not adding each % of pet/dot/nuke up, rather i'm taking the average). If they are increasing a wizards dmg capablities from 18% to 19-25%, that is also about a 1 to 7% increase in dmg.<br /><br />SoE has always aimed for "balancing", in our current state they probably consider our dmg outputs around the same (in my experience i think they are or maybe tipped a little in our favor (once again I realise these are just my experiences and that maybe its alot different for other necromancers, just trying to get across my point though)). So after some thought, making our dot levels 13% would seem a bit excessive. I realise that dots don't make up all our dmg. But since we are getting boosts to all aspects of our dmg (pet, dots and nukes), i'm not sure it would be smart from a developers point of view to make our dots 13% just cause nukes are. In my opinion if i looked at my parses, increased my dot dmg by 13%, my pet and nuke dmg by their respective %'s, and then increased a wizards dmg by 7%, that my dmg would be unbalanced. Once again this is just in my expereience, and I understand that maybe I'm wrong, please post if you disagree.<br /><br />I do agree however that they shouldnt cost so damn much though since we have to spend alot of aas to achieve that same overall dmg increase hehe (SCF3 FoM3 FOMM3 CA3 Petflurry).</span id="msg"></font></td>
