                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Ok, this is my first post ever on this board, or the site for that matter.  I'll try to keep it short and sweet.  I'd like to address a few things said on this topic thus far.  To lead off...<br /><br />1. I don't care whether 12 AAs were easier to get 2 years ago, Pre-Pop, as opposed to now. This topic is reguarding GoD AAs, the here and now. So, let's stick to the here and now..<br /><br />2. As far as it being better to introduce new lines of additional DoT crit AAs in later expansions over time, as opposed to just taking care of the matter with this one, I consider it the responsibility of SoE to take care of all class balancing issues first and foremost.  And this should be a priority above all else, excluding let's say some severe bug that keeps causing a zone to crash or that creates duplicate items etc etc, something immediate and imminently detrimental to EQ as a whole. Waiting until the next expansion to correct a lack of balance just for the sake of waiting...is not acceptable. If you get paid, you do the job...that's how the world (and even EQ's) works.<br /><br />3. Having to spend 30 AAs in order to achieve the same ability to crit as a wizard with 12, is bad math...whether your a Harvard Statistical Mathmatics Ph.D Emeritus, or a 5th grader still trying to figure out the answer to an Algebra 1 problem. And yes, I suspect that at least one or two of you will probably choose to point out (perhaps Waldina)..that I'm comparing apples and oranges, and that's not the only thing a necromancer can do.  Well, that leads to my final...and most important point.<br /><br />4. Utility -- Yes, we as necromancers are easily the most versatile caster archetype in existence. Waldina touched on this briefly in a prior post in this topic, something to the effect of 'I'm not only defined by my dots' (not a literal quote). I agree, certainly.  But now I'm going to turn this word, and this argument around another way. <br /><br />This is mainly a discussion reguarding critical AA's, and to be fair I'll make the comparison strictly in terms of nukes..Wizard vs. Necromancer. The point is, when you look at a wizard or necromancer's nuking crit %age alone, you are not taking into account the *utility* of that number to each class. The only nuke a necromancer has that does any considerable damage to a PoP mob, is Neurotoxin.  Now, let's say Kunsharo is in BoT East with a group killing Vann giants. The geistlig is down to 5%, he's beginning to power up Gate...Neuro fires, then you get this somewhat annoying message --The target resisted your Neurotoxin--.  BoT North? same thing...PoV spiders? same thing. Well, when you can't even land the spell to begin with all the crit AA's in the world won't mean anything. <br /><br />There are *many* areas in PoP, where this spell will not land, at all. The wizard does not have this problem. Why? Because he has his pick of damage...Ice, Fire, Magic etc. If something resists fire, it's almost certainly not going to resist Ice. Once again, the nuking crit AA has more *utility* for that wizard, than Kunsharo (someone may bring up the spell ToM as a nuke, but not only is it mana intensive, I personally use the spell more as a heal/emergency stop-gap in case I draw something's ire..if it crit heals, that's just gravy).<br /><br />The Necromancer has great overall utility, but his ability to nuke...not nearly as great. A %age to crit for a wizard is not the same for a necromancer, even though he has the same number in there. He is a master of nukes, because he has all kinds to draw upon. <br /><br />Now, using that standard...who would be the master of dots? And with that answer in mind, is it fair to make someone spend 30 AAs to be as much a master of dots, as someone with 12 AAs to be a master of nukes.  I leave you to decide...<br /><br />Yes, I do beleive we should have more than one dot crit AA line, and that high number should be significantly closer to 13, than 7.<br /><br />Yeesh, guess that wasn't so short and sweet after all.<br /><br />Later guys ;-)<br /><br />Kunsharo Xyn'Marluuk<br />Arch Lich (65/112), Karana Server<br /><br />      "Those who dare oppose me in life, shall serve me in death..."<br /></span id="msg"></font></td>
                    </tr>
