                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> I agree with many of the posters here.  One thing I do want to mention, is that long ago Dots where better then nukes...in the long run.  They have since become equal.  Wizard and Necromancers doing near (not always) equal damage in the long run.  While if just looking at the numbers, giving us a 13% chance to crit (a basic 13% increase overall, where wizards are getting a 7% boost this time around) may seem unbalanced.  If you look at the fact that we take longer to do the damage, we should do more damage in that regard.  Wizards are short burst high damage (in theory) Necromancers primary damage is long duration damage (hints Damage over time).  <br /><br />In the long run a Necromancer should exceed a Wizard's damage, but only in long fights, wizards would still have the upper hand in short fights, we would exceed in long fights.  <br /><br />Give us the 13% chance like everyone is asking for, we've waited long enough, and it would not be unbalancing in the fact that Dots SHOULD be more efficient in the long run.  As far as the AA cost, I agree that is should a step just like the Nuke crits are, should be the same cost, unless they plan to adjust the cost of those AAs to reflect the new "price"<br /><br />Dechienne Shai'Tan<br /><br />Edit: I can't speel</span id="msg"></font></td>
